Parameter.Name: MamaDelayPeriod
Parameter.Comment: This is the delay period specified in seconds.

Parameter.Name: MamaDelayTickInterval
Parameter.Comment: This is the period over which a block data is cached and replayed. This time is specified in seconds. If the period is 100ms, then all data recorded during that 100ms period, will be stored together and later all will be replayed together. The smaller that this period is, the closer replay will mimic real-time behaviour.

Parameter.Name: MamaDelayMaxFileSize
Parameter.Comment: This is the maximum file size used for the delay cache. This is specified in Kilobytes.

Parameter.Name: MamaDelayFilePath
Parameter.Comment: This is the directory where the data files will be written. It must exist and be writable.

Parameter.Name: MamaDictTransport
Parameter.Comment: Input data dictionary

Parameter.Name: CreateWombatmwInternalThread
Parameter.Comment: Set to true when using WMW (TCP) transport

Parameter.Name: RecordNotFoundAction
Parameter.Comment: This allows requests to go upstream for symbols not yet in cache

Parameter.Name: GroupNotFoundAction
Parameter.Comment: This allows requests to go upstream for symbols not yet in cache

Parameter.Name: MamaSourceConfigurationIsRequired
Parameter.Comment: This must be true for SuperBook and will enforce strict checking for source-related configuration errors.

Parameter.Name: CreateMamaSourceManagerTransports
Parameter.Comment: Create all transports defined in MamaSources during start-up. Set to false if not using all transports defined, or remove unused MamaSource definitions.
